== Welcome to Prometheus 2.0

== Setup and run

Install:
* Ruby 1.9.1
* ruby-rpm
* Ruby on Rails 2.3.4
* PostgreSQL 8.3 (with other databases it doesn't tested)
* ruby-gettext
* ruby-locale

Or, under ALT Linux Sisyphus:
* apt-get install postgresql8.3
* apt-get install postgresql8.3-server
* apt-get install ruby
* apt-get install ruby-rpm
* apt-get install ruby-rails
* apt-get install ruby-activerecord-postgresql-adapter
* apt-get install ruby-activerecord-sqlite3-adapter (for tests)
* apt-get install ruby-gettext_rails
* apt-get install ruby-gettext_rails-tools

Prepare:
* rake makemo

Init database:
* rake db:create
* rake db:migrate
* rake db:seed
* rake sisyphus:groups
* rake sisyphus:srpms
* rake sisyphus:acls
* rake sisyphus:bugs
* rake sisyphus:gitrepos
* rake sisyphus:repocops
* rake sisyphus:leaders
* rake sisyphus:teams
* rake sisyphus:ftbfs_i586
* rake sisyphus:i586
* rake sisyphus:noarch
* rake sisyphus:x86_64

Add to cron:
* 0 0 * * * cd /srv/www/prometheus2.0/current && /usr/bin/rake RAILS_ENV=production sisyphus:update:groups sisyphus:expire:groups >> /var/log/prometheus.log 2>&1


